You might get the packages here to work if you only add libdrm2 and libdrm-intel from the xorg-edgers PPA.     <description>Wine-doors is an application designed to make installing windows software on Linux, Solaris or other Unix systems easier. Wine-doors is essentially a package management tool for windows software on Linux systems. Most Linux desktop users are familiar with package management style application delivery, so it made sense to apply this model to windows software.</description>
